{
  "texts": [
    "In this research, we introduce an advanced training methodology Adversarial DPO (ADPO), which builds upon the principles of Direct Preference Optimization (DPO) as proposed by Rafailov et al. (2023).",
    "The primary aim of ADPO is to mitigate the generation of harmful responses by the model, while preserving overall performance.",
    "This approach is a progression from the conventional DPO, an algorithm offering stability and competitive performance as an alternative to RLHF.",
    "The novelty of ADPO lies in its targeted optimization to reduce the generation of toxic responses.",
    "We hypothesize that training the model with potential toxic responses within its capability range is more effective than using out-of-scope responses."
  ]
}